The National Working Committee (NWC) of the All Progressives Congress (APC) has rescheduled governorship primaries in the Lagos, Enugu and Adamawa states. The primaries in Lagos was rescheduled to hold today but has again been postponed as intrigues continue about the second term of Governor Akinwumi Ambode of Lagos. According to Yekini Nabena, Acting Publicity Secretary of the APC, “the mode of primaries for Enugu and Adamawa states has also been changed from INDIRECT to DIRECT Primaries.” The APC announced that the new dates as follows: Lagos Governorship Primaries – Tuesday, October 2, 2018. Enugu and Adamawa Direct governorship Primaries – Thursday, October 4, 2018. SHOCKING STORY!!! After 9 Years Of Suffering From Weak Erection & Premature Ejaculation, 43 Year Old Man Finally Discovers The Solution That Mysteriously Jerk His Dead Manhood Back To Life, Increased His "Rod" Size, And Now Last 32 Minutes In Bed. Click HERE! 